--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                     Changes in version 2.0.2
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

USER'S OWN DATA SELF EDITING CAN BE DISABLED
Added the settings flag  "disableSelfEdit". If true user cannot edit his 
own profile data

LIMIT ADMINSTRATOR ACCESS ON IP
Added the possibility to limit the admin access by a specific IP address 
(new "adminIP" settings value)

REASSIGN DOCUMENTS AFTER USER DELETION
When a user is deleted his properties (folders, documents, events, etc) can 
be assigned to another user instead to be forced to administrator

SPACE LEFT ON DEVICE 
Added "space used by data" view on backup tools page

Added some user operation control (admin or guest deletion, etc)

The charset=iso-8859-1 use has been signaled on the html head (should fix 
some charset miscoding)

The guest user cannot edit/add events on the calendar

The guest user security has been reinforced (control on a lot of operation,
simplified menus, etc)

Maximum file dimension warning added to document update page

New german translation

Removed a pair of residual "die" instructions

Removed the deprecated split functions (replaced by preg_split)

Removed the deprecated eregi_replace functions (replaced by str_ireplace)

Fixed a bug with "remove version" operation

Corrected calendar (week view) for daylight saving time

The document attachment are now listed ordered (from newer to older)

Modified the viewfolder page icon actions

